[ctns_make id='gen_linear_func_horizontal_line']

  [ctns_front style='']
Horizontal Line
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
If $$y$$ is a constant, then the graph of the linear function is a <strong>horizontal line</strong>; and, the slope of this line is 0.
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
If why is a constant, then the graph of the linear function is a horizontal line -- and, the slope of this line is zero.
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
